analysis: The documents all concern the revocation of previous executive orders that withdrew public lands pending resurvey. Following the revocation, the lands are opened to entry under homestead or desert land laws, with a 91-day priority period for qualified ex-service men. The documents specify the township, range, and meridian of the lands being opened, as well as the applicable Public Resolution.
title: Revoking Land Withdrawals and Prioritizing Veteran Homesteading
